HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 763
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to recognize Siskin Steel & Supply Company,
Inc., on the occasion of its 125th anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those historic Tennessee businesses that have a long-standing commitment to providing
exceptional service to their customers; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable entity is Siskin Steel & Supply Company, Inc., which
celebrates its 125th anniversary this year, a commendable milestone for this notable business;
and
WHEREAS, founded in 1900 in Chattanooga, Siskin Steel & Supply Company began
with a small five-dollar investment and the determination of Robert Siskin, who started collecting
and selling scrap metal to support his family; and
WHEREAS, after the passing of Robert Siskin, his sons, Mose and Garrison Siskin,
expanded the business in 1926, selling new steel and laying the foundation for the full-service
metal supplier the company is today; and
WHEREAS, wholly committed to the precepts of public service, Mose and Garrison
Siskin established what is presently known as the Siskin Children's Institute in 1950 and the
Siskin Hospital for Physical Rehabilitation in 1990; and
WHEREAS, in 1996, Siskin Steel was acquired as a subsidiary of Reliance, Inc., and
since then, the company has expanded to include locations in Nashville, as well as Louisville,
Kentucky, and Spartanburg, South Carolina; and
WHEREAS, Siskin Steel received the Corporate Philanthropy Award from the Siskin
Children's Institute in 2017, a most befitting honor that recognizes the business's dedication to
community service; and
HJR0763
008635
- 1 -

WHEREAS, today, Siskin Steel offers a variety of products, including alloy, aluminum,
carbon steel, and stainless steel, in addition to comprehensive metal processing services; and
WHEREAS, under the current leadership of President Dan Youngman, Siskin Steel &
Supply Company continues to honor its ongoing legacy of support and community partnerships
with local charitable organizations and remains true to its tradition of growth, innovation, and
community impact; and
WHEREAS, for more than twelve decades, Siskin Steel & Supply Company, Inc., has
provided exceptional metal selections, processing services, and superior customer service, and
it is fitting that the business be recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate Siskin Steel & Supply Company, Inc., on 125 years of
operation, wishing the iconic Tennessee business much continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
